04/04/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- Italy and Albania will continue their co-operation in the field of defence, the Italian Experts Delegation (IED) announced in a statement issued Friday (2 April). The statement noted that Italy has drafted several new projects in the field -- two of a general nature, two concerning ground forces, three related to naval forces, and five related to air forces. The IED also announced that Rome had donated equipment to the Central University Military Hospital of Tirana as part of a project in support of the military healthcare system.
In other news, Albania and China have signed a memorandum of co-operation envisioning the bilateral exchange of information on the economic situation and trade opportunities in each country. (ATA - 02/04/04)
